newsitem.title: NETHERLANDS: European feeds trade picks up in afternoon.
newsitem.headline: European feeds trade picks up in afternoon.

text.p: After a dull start trade on the European meals and feeds market picked up ahead of the weekend on a dip in the dollar, market sources said.

"The day started slow with barely changed seller prices and a stronger dollar, but on the dip of the currency later in the day we saw some dealers covering positions ahead of the weekend," one broker said.
Spot Argentine soymeal pellets changed hands at $309 a tonne fob Rotterdam, Brazilian soymeal pellets traded at $316 a tonne cif for Feb shipment and at $299 for March without extension.
